&nbsp;
"Today we are happy with the choice of having left them free in nature", we always read in the post. "A choice for nothing easy or discounted, but the only suit to give it the chance to be two wild marsican bears, both alive at the end of the first winter, even without the mother". "The puppies know how to orient themselves, they do not need food and man need only respect as they did until today," recalls the Park, "without ever forgetting that they are only two specimens of a population of about 60 bears> that they are putting it all to survive. Let us not forget that each of us must also do its part by increasing the knowledge and awareness towards a possible, concrete and above all respectful coexistence". &nbsp;

